commit.message: Bump to 0.14.1.1, update changelog.

Update syntax descriptions from upstream.

For clojure, cmake, coffee, cpp, cs, erlang, graphql, haskell, javascript,
julia, kotlin, lilypond, markdown, objectivec, objectivecpp, ocaml, perl,
python, ruby, rust, stan, typescript, yaml.
Add Skylighting.Syntax.Gpr to skylighting.
Add GPRBuild syntax
Bump skylighting-format-blaze-html to 0.1.1.2, update changelog

Re-add `display: inline-block`, but only to print CSS.

See jgm/pandoc#7248 for an explanation of why this was removed
from the regular CSS, and see jgm/pandoc#9520 for an explanation
of the problems this causes in printed output.
Update changelog for 0.14.1.
Bump to 0.14.1
Don't rely on decodeUtf8Lenient, which is text >= 2 only.
Fix warning.

Regex: handle \Q..\E literal sequences.

Update julia.xml, which was waiting on this feature.

Use Text version of attoparsec to parse regex.

This is needed for proper recognition of unicode characters.

Update raku syntax definition and add patch.

I don't really understand why KDE's version works without this patch.
For now, we can work around it.

Update syntax definitions...

for actionscript, bash, cpp, css, djangotemplate, dosbat,
groovy, ini, isocpp, java, javadoc, json, jsp, latex, makefile,
mustache, php, powershell, rest, rhtml, sass, scala, scss,
toml, xml.

Fix wordDetect to work around an issue in the new html.xml.

Update html syntax definition from upstream.

This uses WordDetect instead of Regex to match `<!DOCTYPE`.
But, officially, there is no word boundary between whitespace
and `<` because `<` is not a word character.  I'm really not
sure why it works in KDE, but the simplest way around this is
simply to disable the checking for a word boundary at the
beginning of the word in `wordDetect`. In practice, a check
at the end should suffice.

Improve Regex to handle some new cases.

We can now handle regexes like `(?i:etc.)`.
Regex: allow unicode char classes outside of [..].

Support one-letter unicode classes like `\p{L}`.

These are found in some of the newer syntax definitions.
I assume `p{L}` matches anything in Lt, Lm, or Lo, and
similarly for `p{M}` etc.
refactor(atWordBoundary): remove redundant checks

fix: atWordBoundary was not strict enough

/x\b/ was behaving like /\bx\b/

fix: lastCharOffset _ 1

Supposing that

1. the string starts with a valid char
2. the offset is a valid char

There is actually exactly one char before offset=1: offset=0.
tests: add failing /u\b/(ue) test
Add comment with link to regex engine documentation.

Don't fail on colors in ARGB format.

We currently just ignore the A part, but at least we don't fail.
Closes #178.

Remove `display: inline-block` from span CSS.

This caused bad results on iOS. Closes #7248.

Bump to 0.1.1.1 and update changelog.
Update changelog.
Add debiancontrol syntax. Closes #173.
Update syntax definitions for bash, cmake, dart, html, markdown, stan.

Bump to 0.14, update changelog.

The version bump is required because we added a rWeakDeliminators
field to the Rule record.

Make WordDetect sensitive to weakDeliminator attribute.

Closes #174. This fixes parsing of C floats beginning with "0."
